    progressionIntro: "A short plan still needs records. Keep setup predictable and progress one variable at a time.",
    progression: ["Add repetitions inside the listed range before load.", "Increase load only when all three sets reach the top of the range.", "If a station is unavailable, use the listed alternative and record it separately.", "When time expires, stop. Do not make the next workout longer to compensate."],
    recovery: ["Avoid placing all three sessions on consecutive days when possible.", "A missed session is a scheduling event, not a failure that requires punishment.", "If 30 minutes is unusually stressful, perform two working sets per exercise and preserve the habit."],
    faq: [{ question: "Is 30 minutes enough to build muscle?", answer: "It can be when the work is challenging, repeated consistently, and progressively overloaded. A shorter session requires tighter exercise selection." }, { question: "Should I use circuits to save time?", answer: "Pairing noncompeting movements is useful, but moving so quickly that repetitions degrade defeats the purpose." }, { question: "What if I have only two days this week?", answer: "Complete the next two sessions in sequence and resume where you stopped. Do not combine all three." }],
